<subSubSection pageId="19" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="19.[108,637,1075,1496]" pageId="19">
ETYMOLOGY: The new genus group name is a combination of 
<emphasis box="[278,344,1109,1132]" italics="true" pageId="19">aporia</emphasis>
(Greek, meaning, “difficult” or “doubt”) and 
<emphasis box="[298,366,1141,1165]" italics="true" pageId="19">cheilos</emphasis>
(Greek, “lip” or “rim”). Although the form of the name is technically a neuter plural, as is that of the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[433,534,1207,1231]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Megachile" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[433,534,1207,1231]" italics="true" pageId="19">Megachile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<superScript attach="right" box="[540,549,1205,1222]" fontSize="7" pageId="19">2</superScript>
the gen- der of the name is here considered to be feminine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
